    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-09-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-11-15T16:08:31Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Reservists' Employment Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow employers a business tax credit for employing a military reservist as a full time employee for a three-year period. Sets the amount of such credit at $1,000 and allows the credit to be taken in the taxable year in which the military reservist's three-year employment period ends. Allows an inflation adjustment to the credit amount after 2005.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
